  "title": "Quality control Engineer (Fabrication /Welding) - *** Freshers / 1 year exp are welcome ***",
  "description": "<p><strong>. QAQC Inspector (Fabrication /Welding)</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>• Preparing or establishing that a welding procedure is available, has been approved as</p><p>required by the appropriate authority and is being employed in production.</p><p>• Witnessing of welder and procedure approval tests that including of the preparation of test</p><p>pieces and destructive tests and verifying compliance with appropriate standards and</p><p>specifications.</p><p>• Verification that adequate and valid welder approvals are available, and that only approved</p><p>welders as required are used in production.</p><p>• Interpretation of weld drawings and weld symbols.</p><p>• Performing of visual inspection and ensure that all finished goods are checked and approved</p><p>prior to any delivery of handover.</p><p>• Verification that post weld heat treatment has been conducted in accordance with</p><p>specification requirements.</p><p>• Appreciation of the factors influencing the formation of weld defects and their acceptability</p><p>in relation to the written specification.</p><p>• Coordination with QC Inspector (Hull/Structure and Piping) and NDT Coordinator, to verify</p><p>and ensure that all finished welds are checked and approved prior to any delivery of</p><p>handover.</p><p>• Ensure that quality assurance standards and procedures are maintained.</p><p>• Ensure that reports that are required are completed accordingly to the project</p><p>specifications.</p><p>• Liaise with Contractor, Production and Client’s representative to ensure the product is</p><p>checked and complied with the project quality plan and specifications.</p><p>• Perform any other tasks as may be assigned by the supervisor.</p><p>• Ensure compliance to relevant government regulations and company’s quality, safety, health</p><p>and environmental (QSHE) policies, practices and procedures at all times.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>• Minimum Diploma in Engineering or relevant field of international certification (e.g. AWSCWI or CSWIP 3.1 WI).</p><p>• Physically fit since some of tasks require lifting of some equipment.</p><p>• A team player with the ability to work independently as well as in a team</p><p>• Good communication skills, meticulous, resourceful, able to multi-task</p><p>• Computer literary (MS. Office).</p>",
